As of 02 Mar 2020 - 05:19:20 AM a 5.5 magnitude earthquake was reported in Leyte.
Instrumental Intensities were recorded in:
Intensity V - Leyte, Kananga, Capoocan, and Pastrana, Leyte; Tacloban City and Ormoc City;
Intensity IV - Palo, Dulag, Babatngon, Alang-alang and Palompon, Leyte;
Mandaue City and Cebu City; Naval, Biliran;
Intensity III - Lapu-lapu City; Lawaan, Eastern Samar;
Intensity IV - Ormoc City; Naval, Biliran; Borongan City;
Intensity II - Bago City;
Intensity I - Masbate City; Roxas City

Expecting aftershocks and damages.

All lifelines are functional. No reported damages as of this time.

Situation Update
•	The storm made landfall at midnight local time (18:30 GMT) on Saturday, near Sagar Island in Indian West Bengal.
•	Seven people were killed in India's West Bengal state, and an eighth person died under a collapsed wall in nearby Odisha state;
•	163,000 people has been evaluated. 112,000 people are in 318 Camp. (In South 24 Parganas:55,000 total, In North 24 Parganas: 43,000 total ,In Purba Medinipur: 23,000 total, In Howrah: 10,000 total, In Hooghly: 9,500 total, In Kolkata: 3,500 total, In Paschim Medinipur: 1,100 total);
•	India's states of West Bengal and Odisha have received heavy rainfall since early Saturday and there were reports of hundreds of trees being uprooted;
•	Kaccha house were damages at Sagar Island, Gosaba, Patharprotima and Basanti area of South 24 Parganas with agriculture lands. Electric facility cut off.
•	The Ministry of Home Affairs of the Government of India is closely monitoring the situation after cyclone Bulbul has hit Eastern India and assured the West Bengal government of full support;
•	10 teams of NDRF in West Bengal and 6 teams in Obisha have been deployed and are assisting the state administration in the evacuation, restoration of roads and in the distribution of relief materials. Additional 18 teams of NDRF have been kept on standby;
•	In the morning on 10 November, several NDRF officials with the chain saw machines were cutting the fallen trees and cleaning up the blocked roads.

