detergents - 203 pcs;

The Ukrainian Red Cross Society is ready to respond to extreme winter conditions in Ukraine. Within 24 hours, to assist the victims, the URCS can mobilize 822 volunteers throughout Ukraine.
The main needs the Ukrainian Red Cross Society are covering:
- Provision of evacuees with heating and protection items from the effects of external weather factors; 
- Food and nutrition;
- Distribution relief items in collective centers;
- Water;
- Helping people during the evacuation;
- Hygiene;
- Arrangement of temporary accommodation for evacuees;
- First aid;
- Providing warm clothes
The URCS has set up warehouse stocks of relief items at regional level all over the country.  
Ten Emergency responce teams have been organized. 
Today, in Ukraine, there are 20 ERTs, consisting with 453-trained volunteers, with all the necessary skills to respond in a crisis and provide first aid to the injured.

